questSteps.stepDescription:
Go up the stairs in Burthorpe Castle. (Chat 1)
Talk to Azzanadra. (Chat ✓)
additionalStepInformation: Make sure you have 4 free inventory slots.

questSteps.stepDescription: Travel to Kharid-et Dig Site. Talk to Azzanadra at the Praetorium war table

Travel to the World Gate and talk to Azzanadra. Equip a face mask to protect against volcanic ash. Having a slayer helmet on the slayer helmet stand counts for this. Enter the World Gate, travelling to the 'Approach' destination (first option). Make sure to finish the dialogue with Azzanadra upon entry.
additionalStepInformation: Teleporting, logging out or going to lobby will require starting this part over from this step.
Enter the World Gate, travelling to the 'Approach' destination (first option).

questSteps.stepDescription: For the time your in this portion of the Approach follow the steps in the Additional Info section and talk to Azzanadra as you progress through. So starting off you enter the Approach talk to Azzanadra.
additionalStepInformation: Head east over the ledges, then up the cliffside.
Continue east, climbing down the drop, then talk to Azzanadra to the south-east. (Chat ~)
Continue north, crossing the stepping stones and up the cliffside.
Continue north, wall run the overhang and talk to Azzanadra again. (Chat ~)
Climb the cliffside, continue west and slide down the slope and head west.
You can heal up by standing under the archway with the glowing crystals.
Continue south, wrapping around east and north, then climb the nearby cliffside which is south of the archway.
Walk across the rock formation and talk to Azzanadra again. (Chat ~)
Continue east and climb down the drop, then traverse the rock bridge to the east.
Talk to Azzanadra again.
Enter the opening.

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Azzanadra.
Inspect the fragmented sphere at each end of the halls.
Talk to Ariane back at the centre, she gives you a blank observation. Azzanadra will replace this if you lost yours.
Collect memories from the elder god memory wisps (50 each). Inspect the blank observation in your backpack after all location wisps are collected. Locations in Additional Info.
additionalStepInformation: Bik memory wisp (western hallway).
Wen memory wisp (northern hallway).
Ful memory wisp (north-eastern hallway).
Jas memory wisp (south-western hallway).

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Azzanadra then Light voice and Shadow voice will speak to you. (Chat 5)
Travel to White Knights' Castle in Falador and enter the courtyard. Talk to Sir Upticious near the entrance.
Go up the eastern ladder then up the staircase by Sir Renitee to the altar in the castle. Talk to Father Frith. (Chat ~)
Go to the 1st floor[US], walk one room west from the ladder and talk to Sir Owen. (Chat ~)
Return upstairs and talk to Father Frith.
Talk to Sir Amik Varze on the 3rd floor[US] in the west wing of the castle. (Chat 1•~)
Talk to Padomenes in the courtyard. (Chat 1•~)
Talk to Sir Vyvin, found next to Father Frith on 3rd floor[US]. (Chat 1)
Talk to Sir Owen on the 1st floor[US]
Search the nearby cupboard. (Chat 1)
Go up the ladder into Sir Renitee's room and crack open the safe then Right-click the slayer bell and use the 'Cut clapper' option to create a silent bell.
Travel to the Paterdomus and enter the Mausoleum to the north.
itemsRecommended: Skeletal Horror Teleport or Invitation Box

questSteps.stepDescription: Use the bell on the well to create a silent bell (blessed).
Return to Saradomin's throne in the White Knights' Castle by the altar and next to Father Frith on 3rd floor[US]. Ring the bell three times, calling Saradomin's name each time. (Chat 1)
Speak to Saradomin. (Chat 3•~•2•1)
Travel to Kharid-et and talk to Azzanadra at the Praetorium war table. (Chat ~)
Travel to the Hall of Memories and enter the pool. (Chat 1•~•~)
Capture the 6 Archivist's memories, then talk to the Archivist (Chat ~•~)
Capture the 6 restricted memories. Interact with each of the plinths in the north-west and north-east. Search the memory bud in the centre to receive a restricted engram.
additionalStepInformation: Capture the 6 restricted memories.
Interact with each of the plinths at the north-west and north-east.
Search the memory bud in the centre to receive a Restricted engram.

questSteps.stepDescription: Leave the Hall of Memories and use the restricted engram on the fountain of energy.
Travel to the entrance of the TzHaar City. Talk to Trindine on the surface of Karamja Volcano
Enter the city, talk to Ga'al right next to the entrance. (Chat ~)
Go to the main plaza (you can teleport back here using the TokKul-Zo), talk to Trindine.
Talk to TokHaar-Hok.
additionalStepInformation: Travel to the TzHaar City library (north-west of the Main Plaza), go inside.

questSteps.stepDescription: Travel to the TzHaar City library (north-west of the main plaza), go inside. Talk to Trindine.
Travel to the Wizards' Tower
Talk to Wizard Trindy on 1st floor[US] at entrance of the Wizards' Tower. (Chat ~)
Search four bookcases to the west.
Talk to Wizard Trindy at the eastern bookcases.
Return to Kharid-et Dig Site's praetorium war table. Talk to Azzanadra.
Travel to the entrance of the Heart of Gielinor. Located west of Nardah
Talk to Azzanadra.
Enter the Heart.
Observe each of the eggs at the end of the corridors then talk to Ariane
additionalStepInformation: Bik's egg.
Wen's egg.
Ful's egg.

questSteps.stepDescription: Return to Kharid-et and enter to the main fortress. (Chat 1) Walk to the praetorium war table. Information on what to do in Additional Info Section.
additionalStepInformation: Stand next to any four shadow anchors around Kharid-et.
Harvest Trindine wisps until you get 50 memories.
Inspect the blank observation and finish the dialogue or Ga'al will not spawn for the next step.

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Ga'al in the main plaza.
Return to the Wizards' Tower and walk to the entrance to trigger the dialogue.
Return to the Hall of Memories and enter the pool. (Chat 1) Talk to the Archivist.
Return to the Heart of Gielinor (enter from the entrance). (Chat 1)

Talk to Ariane. A cutscene will follow. (Chat ~)
then talk to Ariane again.
Return to the White Knights' Castle, talk to Ariane on the bridge to trigger a cutscene. (Chat ~)
Return to Kharid-et, talk to Azzanadra at the praetorium war table to complete the quest.
Quest Complete!
